=== 荒謬 ===
{{Main article|荒謬}}

[[荒謬|荒謬]]這個概念是指世界的不合理部分与我们渴望解释的一切冲突和离异。[[加繆|加繆]]認為，建立在懷疑論之上的生活是没有真正意義的，但接受荒谬的诚实的人会以自己的反抗賦予生活意義。這种無意義性還涵蓋著世界的是非不分與不公平。這與「壞事不會發生在好人身上」的概念相左；對世界而言，打個比方說，沒有所謂的好人或壞人；發生的事就這樣發生了，它可能降臨在任何「好」人或「壞」人身上。<ref name="plato.stanford.edu">Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, Existentialism, [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/existentialism/#AnxNotAbs 3.1 Anxiety, Nothingness, the Absurd] {{Wayback|url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/existentialism/#AnxNotAbs |date=20191019074750 }}</ref>

荒謬這概念一直以來都在文學上相當突出。[[索倫·奧貝·克爾凱郭爾|祁克果]]、[[萨缪尔·贝克特|貝克特]]、[[弗朗茨·卡夫卡|卡夫卡]]、[[費奧多爾·米哈伊洛維奇·陀思妥耶夫斯基|陀思妥耶夫斯基]]、[[欧仁·尤内斯库|尤內斯庫]]、[[米蓋爾·德·烏納穆諾|烏納穆諾]]、[[路伊吉·皮兰德娄|皮藍德羅]]<ref name=luigitheatre>{{cite book|last1=Bassnett|first1=Susan|last2=Lorch|first2=Jennifer|title=Luigi Pirandello in the Theatre|date=March 18, 2014|publisher=Routledge|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FpwiAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA182&dq=luigi+pirandello+existentialism&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oIQTVb7lDMnxoASF14LIAQ&ved=0CDwQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=existentialist&f=false|accessdate=26 March 2015|archive-date=2021-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205011028/https://books.google.com/books?id=FpwiAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA182&dq=luigi+pirandello+existentialism&hl=en&sa=X&ei=oIQTVb7lDMnxoASF14LIAQ&ved=0CDwQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=existentialist&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=understandex>{{cite book|last1=Thompson|first1=Mel|last2=Rodgers|first2=Nigel|title=Understanding Existentialism: Teach Yourself|date=2010|publisher=Hodder & Stoughton|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vfczAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT105&dq=pirandello+existentialism&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ZIYTVZSCK5CeoQT_poLgBA&ved=0CDQQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existentialism&f=false|access-date=2017-08-19|archive-date=2021-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205012114/https://books.google.com/books?id=vfczAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT105&dq=pirandello+existentialism&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ZIYTVZSCK5CeoQT_poLgBA&ved=0CDQQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existentialism&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=crisisconsciousness>{{cite book|last1=Caputi|first1=Anthony Francis|title=Pirandello and the Crisis of Modern Consciousness|date=1988|publisher=University of Illinois Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0Qv2nuJF7yYC&pg=PA80&dq=pirandello+existential+absurd&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4YYTVYCyJcrVoAS9_IKwBA&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existentialist%20absurdity&f=false|access-date=2017-08-19|archive-date=2021-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210220211722/https://books.google.com/books?id=0Qv2nuJF7yYC&pg=PA80&dq=pirandello+existential+absurd&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4YYTVYCyJcrVoAS9_IKwBA&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existentialist%20absurdity&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=masks>{{cite book|last1=Mariani|first1=Umberto|title=Living Masks: The Achievement of Pirandello|date=2010|publisher=University of Toronto Press|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vBviYn43H34C&pg=PT178&dq=pirandello+existential+absurd&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4YYTVYCyJcrVoAS9_IKwBA&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existential%20absurd&f=false|accessdate=26 March 2015|archive-date=2021-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210205011146/https://books.google.com/books?id=vBviYn43H34C&pg=PT178&dq=pirandello+existential+absurd&hl=en&sa=X&ei=4YYTVYCyJcrVoAS9_IKwBA&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=pirandello%20existential%20absurd&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[萨特|萨特]]、[[约瑟夫·海勒|海勒]]和[[加缪|加缪]]的許多文學作品都在描述人遭遇到世界的荒謬。

在痛苦地察覺到此無意義後，[[加繆|加繆]]在《[[西绪弗斯神话|薛西弗斯的神話]]》中稱「真正嚴肅的哲學問題只有一個，就是自殺。」雖然針對這類可能極度有害遭遇的「藥方」各自不同，不論是祁克果的宗教「階段」或[[加繆|加繆]]的堅持不懈，大多數存在主義哲學家的焦點都在幫助人們避開不好的生活方式，以免置於喪失一切意義的長期險境之中。這種意義崩解的可能性會對自身[[寂靜主義|平靜]]構成重要威脅，而這也就違背存在主義的哲學。<ref>{{cite web |author=Jean-Paul Sartre |url=http://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/sartre/works/exist/sartre.htm |title=Existentialism is a Humanism, Jean-Paul Sartre 1946 |publisher=Marxists.org |accessdate=2010-03-08 |archive-date=2011-06-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614220253/http://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/sartre/works/exist/sartre.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>據信因自殺是可能的而使得所有人都是存在主義者。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Suicide and Self-Deception|author=E Keen|publisher=Psychoanalytic Review|year=1973|url=http://www.pep-web.org/document.php?id=PSAR.060.0575A|postscript=<!-- Bot inserted parameter. Either remove it; or change its value to "." for the cite to end in a ".", as necessary. -->|access-date=2017-08-19|archive-date=2018-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918184933/http://www.pep-web.org/document.php?id=PSAR.060.0575A|dead-url=no}}</ref>在無意義的生活中，一個荒誕主義者能不屈地直面“自殺”。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Suicide and Self-Deception|author=E Keen|publisher=Psychoanalytic Review|year=1973|url=http://www.pep-web.org/document.php?id=PSAR.060.0575A|postscript=<!-- Bot inserted parameter. Either remove it; or change its value to "." for the cite to end in a ".", as necessary. -->|access-date=2017-08-19|archive-date=2018-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918184933/http://www.pep-web.org/document.php?id=PSAR.060.0575A|dead-url=no}}</ref>

